==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pulmotor
<hw>Pul"mo`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pulmo</ets> lung + E. <ets>motor</ets>.]</ety> <def>An apparatus
for producing artificial respiration by pumping oxygen or air or a
mixture of the two into and out of the lungs, as of a person who has
been asphyxiated by drowning, breathing poisonous gases, or the like, or
of one who has been stunned by an electrical shock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pulp</ent>⟦br⟧
